      "",
      "{/*",
      "  SOURCE OF TRUTH PAGE TEMPLATE",
      "  ─────────────────────────────",
      "  Use this template for any canonical reference page that documents how a system",
      "  or category of artifacts is classified, structured, enforced, and maintained.",
      "",
      "  Scope: one governed system per page (e.g. components, scripts, templates, AI tools).",
      "",
      "  Replace all [Topic], [item], [items], [category-x] placeholders throughout.",
      "  Update the import paths if different component files are needed.",
      "*/}",
      "",
      "## Overview",
      "",
      "{/* One paragraph: what system does this page govern, who it's for, and what the reader gets. */}",
      "",
      "This is the canonical reference for **[Topic]** in the Livepeer docs repo.",
      "It covers classification rules, folder structure, naming conventions, enforcement policies, and governance.",
      "Use this page to find, build, modify, or audit [items].",
      "",
      "<CustomDivider />",
      "",
      "## Repo Context & Folders",
      "",
      "{/* Show where the governed artifacts live. Expand the tree to the depth that's useful — not exhaustive. */}",
      "",
      "<Tree>",
      "  <Folder name=\"path/to/governed-folder\" defaultOpen>",
      "    <Folder name=\"category-a\">",
      "      <File name=\"Example.jsx\" />",
      "    </Folder>",
      "    <Folder name=\"category-b\">",
      "      <File name=\"Example.jsx\" />",
      "    </Folder>",
      "    <File name=\"README.md\" />",
      "  </Folder>",
      "</Tree>",
      "",
      "<CustomDivider />",
      "",
      "## Framework & Standards",
      "",
      "{/*",
      "  One row per category or type.",
      "  Columns: Category | Description | Repo Location | Example artifact",
      "*/}",
      "",
      "<StyledTable>",
      "  <TableRow header>",
      "    <TableCell>Category</TableCell>",
      "    <TableCell>Description</TableCell>",
      "    <TableCell>Repo Location</TableCell>",
      "    <TableCell>Example</TableCell>",
      "  </TableRow>",
